, 
<bibRefCitation id="87FE4E7B7630E77746D0EEF3217B8956" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="10" pageNumber="95" pagination="903 - 927" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea). III. Revision of the genera Zonioploca Stal and Eppertia Shaw." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9650903" volume="13" year="1965 c">1965c</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F661B5A37330CF7250FF50552455B13F" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="10" pageNumber="95" pagination="305 - 324" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea). IV Megazosteria, gen. nov., and revision of the genera Desmozosteria Shelford." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9660305" volume="14" year="1966 a">1966a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="DA0601917AE278C627E495F85E50F5B4" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="10" pageNumber="95" pagination="335 - 363" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea). V. Revision of the genera Anamesia Tepper and Pseudolampra Tepper." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9660335" volume="14" year="1966 b">1966b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F9F2CEF980FD746693B57A33D01E757A" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="10" pageNumber="95" pagination="593 - 618" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea). VI. Revision of the genus Cosmozosteria Stal." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9670593" volume="15" year="1967 a">1967a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A9622952125062CE03E7824EDAFA86E8" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="10" pageNumber="95" pagination="1207 - 1298" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea). VII. The Platyzosteria group; general remarks and revision of the subgenera Platyzosteria Brunner and Leptozosteria Tepper." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9671207" volume="15" year="1967 b">1967b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E4AD6C39BF0D5C2B1BE3F11205E0E15C" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="10" pageNumber="95" pagination="237 - 331" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea). VIII. The Platyzosteria group; subgenus Melanozostera Stal." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680237" volume="16" year="1968 a">1968a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B611895BE72E01522027AA4CC56C43E9" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="10" pageNumber="95" pagination="511 - 575" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea). IX. Revision of Polyzosteriinae tribe Methanini, Tryonicinae, and Blattinae." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" volume="16" year="1968 b">1968b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="A364DBE7BA0CEE7424C05060375A7258" author="Rehn, JAG" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="10" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 320" title="The Orthoptera of the West Indies. Number 1. Blattidae." volume="54" year="1927">Rehn and Hebard 1927</bibRefCitation>
), the 
<taxonomicName id="25A5F27A7A0C88971E3824DE02AEA15C" lsidName="" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
is characterized as follows: species having semicircular pronotum, lobiform vestigial tegmina, angles of T2-T7 produced, tarsi usually short, bare or with hind and sometimes mid metatarsi spiny (
<taxonomicName id="E76CA89D659A987302589BB9F960A4E5" authority="Liao, Wang &amp; Che, 2019" authorityName="Liao, Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Laevifacies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Laevifacies" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Laevifacies</taxonomicName>
with mid and hind metatarsi spiny, while in 
<bibRefCitation id="D18BA9CBEBE8C06312D1BE8DC53A197D" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="10" pageNumber="95" pagination="511 - 575" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea). IX. Revision of Polyzosteriinae tribe Methanini, Tryonicinae, and Blattinae." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" volume="16" year="1968 b">Mackerras (1968b)</bibRefCitation>
, Australian species of 
<taxonomicName id="747F27104BCCBA7076F15B9FE2B23095" lsidName="" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Blattinae">Blattinae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1D89C933EBDAD58CAAB65C72BBCA2C1B" lsidName="" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
from other 
<taxonomicName id="DE4E6AE615511AC63104AB15D8A3F99F" family="Blattidae" lsidName="" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" rank="family">Blattidae</taxonomicName>
with all metatarsi spiny), large pulvilli and arolia, cerci strong, short and symmetrical, L1 with hollow finger-like projection and sclerotized projection and R1 claw-like and margin with projection; thus, 
<taxonomicName id="A450579A456A4ADA4E5EC8B9AB5E2B2E" authority="Liao, Wang &amp; Che, 2019" authorityName="Liao, Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Laevifacies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Laevifacies" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Laevifacies</taxonomicName>
is placed in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="6060FC766BCDB6DE5BEB974D1E60BDF7" lsidName="" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="0D49F4CC794861CE4059C22A79501C1D" authority="Liao, Wang &amp; Che, 2019" authorityName="Liao, Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Laevifacies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Laevifacies" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Laevifacies</taxonomicName>
has common features with 
<taxonomicName id="AF6B3785779C532201BF67C9EF1E6F8B" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melanozosteria</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CD61E599AA379A5EF07C84745501C5C6" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Eurycotis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurycotis" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eurycotis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E1A0397C37FA83A4EB1D9DF6827984BB" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Leptozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leptozosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Leptozosteria</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="451D1794DDFA7D473B3D3052DA55B098" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Platyzosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platyzosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Platyzosteria</taxonomicName>
, such as body small to large, and shining, usually with vestigial tegmina, angles of T5-T6 acute, T6-T7 with punctation and hind metatarsus usually spiny (
<bibRefCitation id="12EBBFA82B402E5E8B665B707CB18298" author="Gutierrez, E" journalOrPublisher="Novitates Caribaea" pageId="10" pageNumber="95" pagination="16 - 35" title="El genero Eurycotis (Dictyoptera: Blattaria: Blattidae: Polyzosteriinae) 1. Especies de la Hispaniola. Primera parte: seis especies nuevas." volume="2013" year="2013">
<normalizedToken id="2B2EDADCC08E1F4109DF7A2A6FD1E2BA" originalValue="Gutiérrez">Gutierrez</normalizedToken>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F9FCF7896C270FDC6441C9C952DA153C" author="Gutierrez, E" journalOrPublisher="Novitates Caribaea" pageId="10" pageNumber="95" pagination="1 - 21" title="El genero Eurycotis (Dictyoptera: Blattaria: Blattidae: Polyzosteriinae) 1. Especies de la Hispaniola. Segunda parte: siete especies nuevas." volume="2014" year="2014">2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="84DF1F54C5903E5275F451CFA1FAD0D6" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="10" pageNumber="95" pagination="903 - 927" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea). III. Revision of the genera Zonioploca Stal and Eppertia Shaw." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9650903" volume="13" year="1965 c">Mackerras 1965c</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="2D4AD17813221421806F4C2C4335479C" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="10" pageNumber="95" pagination="511 - 575" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea). IX. Revision of Polyzosteriinae tribe Methanini, Tryonicinae, and Blattinae." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" volume="16" year="1968 b">1968b</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4931457A37264D732CF9083B9EEFC721" authority="Liao, Wang &amp; Che, 2019" authorityName="Liao, Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Laevifacies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Laevifacies" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Laevifacies</taxonomicName>
is similar to the 
<taxonomicName id="512076B5C5799E8BBB1CA67D11A370CD" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melanozosteria</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="989262C8D100F16E5D7C390BB7819386" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Eurycotis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurycotis" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eurycotis</taxonomicName>
in general appearance, but it can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="66B6FB153DF10E8B769123BD6C495B20" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melanozosteria</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: 1) body thin and small in male (Figure 2A, B), while in 
<taxonomicName id="87A76A0A660383829A13D57DD2195669" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melanozosteria</taxonomicName>
, it is broad and large (Figure 4A, B, F, G); 2) the surface of terga smooth (Figure 2A), vs. surface with punctation in 
<taxonomicName id="FF10AB98133210B131D33CFC226B44FE" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melanozosteria</taxonomicName>
(Figure 4A, F); 3) male with vestigial tegmina and hind wings (Figure 2A), but in 
<taxonomicName id="B3C746A0038147CA3BA67E5EA814361A" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melanozosteria</taxonomicName>
only with vestigial tegmina or apterous (Figure 4A, F); 4) the margin of L2d smooth and posterior of L2d finger-like with more small spines (Figure 3A), while in 
<taxonomicName id="9477A76875B7DB63A04369F4624E7869" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melanozosteria</taxonomicName>
the margin strongly denticulate and posterior of L2d with acute angle (Figure 4J, M); 5) L3 bifurcated, one short and the other long (Figure 3A), however, L3 unbifurcated or bifurcated with branches of equal length in 
<taxonomicName id="B53E9B0C3F2A1F8AA32133E550B2DADA" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melanozosteria</taxonomicName>
(Figure 4J, M); 6) R1 fist-shaped (Figure 3C), while in 
<taxonomicName id="E6506BF0EA773B53EB63ECE9E83FBE72" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melanozosteria</taxonomicName>
foot-shaped or finger-shaped (Figure 4K, M); and 7) R2 only with one large and long uniform structure (Figure 3C), while in 
<taxonomicName id="43971F335F4D8B6EA5B03BF53159791B" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Melanozosteria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanozosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Melanozosteria</taxonomicName>
, two unequal forked structures present (Figure 4K, M); and it can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="3D5853209328B5B73F1BD8EE0ECE897B" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Eurycotis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurycotis" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eurycotis</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: 1) tibiae not specialized, while in 
<taxonomicName id="99D33EA1C317EDC93902485D2DD71BBF" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Eurycotis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurycotis" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eurycotis</taxonomicName>
, one group of which species have smooth surface, uniform black body and lateral tegmina, with highly specialized caudal tibiae; 2) R2 is hook-like, while in 
<taxonomicName id="EFE851AFB67DEA9095F2581F1F165F75" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Eurycotis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurycotis" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eurycotis</taxonomicName>
R2 is pincer-like. In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="1AB2F6C58AD30CD95F88DD1A189F2E57" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Eurycotis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eurycotis" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eurycotis</taxonomicName>
is restricted to South and North America and Cuba, while 
<taxonomicName id="2631F553886936E7C55331E9E0F48422" authority="Liao, Wang &amp; Che, 2019" authorityName="Liao, Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Laevifacies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Laevifacies" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Laevifacies</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. is found in East Asia. 
<taxonomicName id="34E9F531802AD50254B5F694630B4765" authority="Liao, Wang &amp; Che, 2019" authorityName="Liao, Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Laevifacies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Laevifacies" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Laevifacies</taxonomicName>
is similar to the 
<taxonomicName id="DE82A30C325C970CC9C991406B4DE355" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Methana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Methana" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Methana</taxonomicName>
in the following genitalia characteristics, the margin of L2d smooth, R1 as a strongly claw-like sclerotized process, both of L1 have two structures, L1 of 
<taxonomicName id="876BF5DE3E645B11F93FEFDF0D9A329D" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Methana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Methana" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Methana</taxonomicName>
has strong finger-like sclerotization and a membranous lobe, while 
<taxonomicName id="3180155B1B86C8D953440AE7344C3B30" authority="Liao, Wang &amp; Che, 2019" authorityName="Liao, Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Laevifacies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Laevifacies" order="Blattodea" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Laevifacies</taxonomicName>
has a finger-like membrane and a strongly sclerotized lobe (Figure 3A, B).
</paragraph>
